Summer is here!  I’m sharing some tips on how to keep a double coated dog cool during the summer months.

Most people think the coat is like a sweater keeping their dog hot, but it’s actually more like insulation! And cutting a double coat actually damages the coat. Brushing out the undercoat will help their skin breathe and keep them cozy. 

So my biggest tips to help your double coated dog stay cool in the summer is by keeping them clean, conditioned, and brushed out.
